00:17:52,580 --> 00:17:54,460
I want to talk to you properly.

279
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,080
You force me to sue you.

280
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:20,710
I get it.

281
00:18:27,170 --> 00:18:29,130
The court will assess the income

282
00:18:29,130 --> 00:18:30,040
and property status of both parents

283
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:31,380
to ensure the child

284
00:18:31,380 --> 00:18:34,750
can grow up in a stable and comfortable environment.

285
00:18:35,630 --> 00:18:40,000
The mom is still more attentive to the child.

286
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,250
No, no, he's pretty good.

287
00:18:42,250 --> 00:18:43,500
He's taken care of Mumu for five years.

288
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:45,130
Isn't Mumu doing well?

289
00:18:45,130 --> 00:18:47,670
But when Mumu goes to school,

290
00:18:47,670 --> 00:18:48,790
we can't teach her.

291
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:50,750
Everyone here likes Mumu, we can all take care of her.

292
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,830
Your ex-wife is going to sue you.

293
00:18:53,830 --> 00:18:55,000
What can you do?

294
00:18:55,130 --> 00:18:57,630
Yeah, where's the money coming from?

295
00:18:57,630 --> 00:19:00,380
Aren't we trying to find a solution right now?

296
00:19:02,420 --> 00:19:05,000
You don't want Mumu to go with her mom, do you?

297
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:08,880
So you're determined to go to court, huh?

298
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,540
Do you know any lawyers?

299
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:16,380
Do you?

300
00:19:18,670 --> 00:19:20,380
I do.

301
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,130
Didn't Mr. Zhao come?

302
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:47,500
What would he come for?

303
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:49,040
He can't translate anyway.

304
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:51,170
Carry this.

305
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:06,880
I've already done my part,

306
00:20:07,290 --> 00:20:08,250
and you still expect me to drive?

307
00:20:09,290 --> 00:20:10,130
Wait a minute.

308
00:20:13,630 --> 00:20:14,500
You drive.

309
00:20:20,630 --> 00:20:21,040
I know

310
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:22,500
hearing aids are useless for you.

311
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:24,000
Just put on a show for the police.

312
00:20:44,670 --> 00:20:45,170
Didn't they say

313
00:20:45,290 --> 00:20:47,880
you get the driver's license quite early?

314
00:20:48,460 --> 00:20:50,000
Your driving is terrible.

315
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,000
Speed up.

316
00:21:16,210 --> 00:21:18,380
Custody was awarded to Mr. Ma during the divorce.

317
00:21:18,420 --> 00:21:19,330
In principle,

318
00:21:19,330 --> 00:21:21,710
it's quite difficult to overturn that now.

319
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:23,830
Because the child is under eight years old,

320
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:25,000
the court won't give too much weight to

321
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,210
her opinion.

322
00:21:26,380 --> 00:21:26,880
In other words,

323
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,880
even if she expresses a desire to live with you,

324
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:30,210
the court may not listen.

325
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,710
So there's really no other way?

326
00:21:33,710 --> 00:21:34,710
Don't worry too much.

327
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,580
As long as no child abuse has taken place,

328
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:39,250
the court usually won't change the ruling.

329
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:40,000
I see.

330
00:21:40,380 --> 00:21:42,380
So things aren't that bad, right?

331
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:43,080
No.

332
00:21:43,130 --> 00:21:45,080
Okay, I'll pass that on.

333
00:21:49,210 --> 00:21:51,330
The lawyer said it will be difficult

334
00:21:51,330 --> 00:21:54,210
for you to win the case.

335
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,750
Why?

336
00:21:57,750 --> 00:22:00,130
Mumu and I are very happy together.

337
00:22:00,130 --> 00:22:02,080
What's the point of that?

338
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:04,710
You two sleep in a mahjong parlor.

339
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:06,250
You don't have any stable income either.

340
00:22:06,250 --> 00:22:08,000
Mumu isn't going to school.

341
00:22:08,630 --> 00:22:11,130
Compared to her mother… you're definitely going to lose.

342
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:14,580
If the parent who lives with the child

343
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:15,710
has a serious illness

344
00:22:15,830 --> 00:22:17,290
or is unable to continue to raise the child

345
00:22:17,290 --> 00:22:17,830
due to disability,

346
00:22:17,830 --> 00:22:19,210
or abuses the child

347
00:22:19,250 --> 00:22:20,170
and causes serious harm to the child's physical

348
00:22:20,170 --> 00:22:21,710
or mental health,

349
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:23,130
the court will support a change in the ruling.

350
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:25,210
No.

351
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:26,330
I'll work hard.

352
00:22:26,330 --> 00:22:29,460
I'll give Mumu the best.

353
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:32,000
I'll make money to send Mumu to school.

354
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,330
How are you going to make money in such a short time?

355
00:22:34,330 --> 00:22:36,330
I'll try my best. I can do it, really.

356
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:37,960
What did he say?
Why is he looking at me like that?

357
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,960
Just cooperate with me and nod slightly.

358
00:22:45,130 --> 00:22:48,420
Attorney Chen agrees to help you.

359
00:22:48,420 --> 00:22:50,380
He's good at this type of case.

360
00:22:51,580 --> 00:22:52,460
Really?

361
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:57,880
Thank you so much.

362
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:01,960
But the reality is

363
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,250
Mr. Ma hasn't been sending his daughter to school,

364
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:06,460
and their living environment is quite poor.

365
00:23:06,580 --> 00:23:08,080
We can figure something out here.

366
00:23:08,130 --> 00:23:08,460
Of course,

367
00:23:08,460 --> 00:23:10,710
if we go down this road, it's going to be hurtful.

368
00:23:11,460 --> 00:23:12,830
You need to be prepared for that.

369
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:14,460
Tell him

370
00:23:14,750 --> 00:23:15,960
that he absolutely cannot

371
00:23:15,960 --> 00:23:17,250
live in the mahjong parlor anymore.

372
00:23:17,580 --> 00:23:19,330
Tell him to find a stable job as soon as possible.

373
00:23:19,460 --> 00:23:21,710
And then send his daughter to school right away.

374
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:23,210
Thank you, Attorney Chen. Thank you.

375
00:23:26,630 --> 00:23:30,330
Attorney Chen has agreed to help you but expensive.

376
00:23:30,460 --> 00:23:31,630
Can you afford it?

377
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,130
How much is it?

378
00:23:44,210 --> 00:23:50,790
(Hong Jie, can you ask about hotel work?)

379
00:23:50,790 --> 00:23:51,920
(Sending to Hong Jie)

380
00:23:53,040 --> 00:23:56,920
(Hong Jie: Positions available, benefits are good. Bring Mumu over here!)

381
00:23:59,790 --> 00:24:01,210
The two of you,

382
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:03,710
I can only choose one?

383
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:08,580
Can't I have both a mom and a dad?

384
00:24:09,330 --> 00:24:13,710
I'll behave. Can't I have both of your if I go to school?

385
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:21,960
Mom…

386
00:24:22,630 --> 00:24:24,960
why doesn't she want us anymore?

387
00:24:25,250 --> 00:24:29,830
It's not like that. She always wants you.

388
00:24:30,460 --> 00:24:31,750
She…

389
00:24:34,330 --> 00:24:38,130
She just doesn't want me anymore.

390
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:39,920
You want me to pretend to be your wife?

391
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:40,710
What are you thinking?

392
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:42,580
Not my wife. Mumu's mom.

393
00:24:42,580 --> 00:24:43,880
Help me.

394
00:24:45,630 --> 00:24:47,880
Please.

395
00:24:56,830 --> 00:24:59,080
Please, help me.

396
00:24:59,580 --> 00:25:01,000
You're the only translator I know.

397
00:25:01,330 --> 00:25:02,460
It's too much trouble. I don't do this.

398
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:03,710
I don't like kids.

399
00:25:04,460 --> 00:25:06,080
I can pay you.

400
00:25:06,130 --> 00:25:07,750
I don't want your money. Get out.

401
00:25:09,500 --> 00:25:13,000
My dad has a motorcycle that he never washes.

402
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:14,960
I taught her ancient poems.

403
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:16,130
He goes looking for job

404
00:25:16,130 --> 00:25:18,790
with lots of balloons tied to his back.

405
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:23,420
He just runs around, not understanding anything.

406
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:28,290
He still has to rely on my wits to solve big problems.

407
00:25:32,250 --> 00:25:33,250
Is that okay?

408
00:25:54,710 --> 00:25:55,460
Mumu,

409
00:25:55,750 --> 00:25:57,380
what's three plus two?

410
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,830
We can do addition and subtraction within a hundred.

411
00:26:09,460 --> 00:26:10,210
Mumu,

412
00:26:11,330 --> 00:26:13,210
do you like drawing whales?

413
00:26:13,210 --> 00:26:14,380
Who taught you to draw?

414
00:26:16,330 --> 00:26:17,250
Probably got it from me.

415
00:26:19,630 --> 00:26:21,080
Yes, she seems to have artistic talent.

416
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:23,790
Mumu,

417
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:26,750
can you answer my question?

418
00:26:31,330 --> 00:26:32,130
Mumu,

419
00:26:32,830 --> 00:26:34,250
let's recite a poem for the teacher.

420
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:35,960
My daughter is very smart.

421
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:37,000
She can recite more than ten poems.

422
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:38,580
Just recite the one you're best at.

423
00:26:39,830 --> 00:26:40,580
Hurry up.

424
00:26:43,380 --> 00:26:45,380
Doesn't she speak a little...

425
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:46,380
She has no problem speaking.

426
00:26:46,500 --> 00:26:47,580
She's like a little chatterbox at home.

427
00:26:47,580 --> 00:26:48,710
She talks a lot.

428
00:26:48,710 --> 00:26:51,540
She's probably just a little nervous today.

429
00:26:54,130 --> 00:26:55,580
But if she doesn't speak at all,

430
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:56,880
we can't really make a determination.

431
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:58,630
Maybe you should try another school.

432
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:00,750
I'm sorry,

433
00:27:00,750 --> 00:27:02,380
I have to get ready for class.

434
00:27:03,750 --> 00:27:04,580
What happened?
She didn't speak.

435
00:27:06,330 --> 00:27:07,130
Teacher,

436
00:27:08,790 --> 00:27:09,580
all these years...

437
00:27:11,130 --> 00:27:13,000
All these years he's been raising the child alone.

438
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:14,960
It's been quite difficult.

439
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:19,330
As you know, he's deaf.

440
00:27:19,630 --> 00:27:20,710
He hasn't had much formal schooling,

441
00:27:21,710 --> 00:27:24,670
but he hopes his daughter can have an education,

442
00:27:24,670 --> 00:27:26,330
and grow up like a normal child.

443
00:27:28,540 --> 00:27:29,960
He can't hear Mumu's voice,

444
00:27:31,580 --> 00:27:32,880
so he can only memorize

445
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:34,790
every poem, the mouth shape of every word.

446
00:27:35,500 --> 00:27:37,630
And then he checks one by one.

447
00:27:38,250 --> 00:27:39,380
He even records Mumu reciting poems

448
00:27:39,380 --> 00:27:40,540
and asks others to listen to them

449
00:27:40,540 --> 00:27:41,540
and tell him if she recited them correctly.

450
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,080
Get the recording pen.

451
00:27:51,130 --> 00:27:53,580
Wild grass on the distant plain.

452
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:56,330
It withers and grows every year.

453
00:27:56,830 --> 00:27:59,080
Though scorched by wild fire,

454
00:27:59,330 --> 00:28:01,500
the spring breeze revives it again.

455
00:28:01,710 --> 00:28:03,880
Sweet fragrance invades the ancient road.

456
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:06,130
Fresh green meets the ruined city.

457
00:28:06,460 --> 00:28:08,460
Another farewell to a noble youth,

458
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:10,630
the grass grows thick with parting sorrow.

459
00:28:20,130 --> 00:28:21,830
How much can you earn from your new job?

460
00:28:22,210 --> 00:28:23,960
Attorney Chen is waiting.

461
00:28:24,630 --> 00:28:26,830
Soon, just wait a little longer.

462
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:29,000
Hurry up.

463
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,250
The court doesn't wait for you.

464
00:28:30,380 --> 00:28:32,170
What's a lawsuit?

465
00:28:32,710 --> 00:28:34,790
There is a judge

466
00:28:34,790 --> 00:28:38,830
who decides whether you live with me or mom.

467
00:28:38,830 --> 00:28:42,210
I don't want others to decide who I'm with.

468
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:45,000
I don't want others to decide either.

469
00:28:46,580 --> 00:28:50,830
Are you happy living with me?

470
00:28:54,830 --> 00:28:56,580
Unhappy?

471
00:28:57,330 --> 00:29:00,750
I'm happy.

472
00:29:02,500 --> 00:29:04,250
Even though you have a lot of flaws,

473
00:29:04,460 --> 00:29:05,960
you're a good dad.

474
00:29:10,500 --> 00:29:12,210
If we have to go to court,

475
00:29:12,210 --> 00:29:13,830
I'll tell the judge

476
00:29:13,830 --> 00:29:15,960
I want to live with you.

477
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:19,210
Really?

478
00:29:19,380 --> 00:29:21,710
If I go back on my word, I'm a piglet.

479
00:29:22,250 --> 00:29:24,380
Pig, pig, pig.

480
00:29:24,830 --> 00:29:27,000
Pig, pig, pig.

481
00:29:41,210 --> 00:29:42,830
This is for when she goes to school.

482
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:47,630
This is to keep her healthy.

483
00:29:51,540 --> 00:29:53,290
You must study hard.

484
00:29:53,380 --> 00:29:56,830
Listen to your dad. I love you.

485
00:30:00,380 --> 00:30:02,630
You must study well.

486
00:30:18,290 --> 00:30:20,920
Don't bring Mumu back again.

487
00:30:21,790 --> 00:30:24,000
Live well and remember us.

488
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,580
Remember us.

489
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:37,500
Have a safe journey.

490
00:31:05,540 --> 00:31:06,710
Is this your car?

491
00:31:07,540 --> 00:31:08,920
It's cool, huh?

492
00:31:11,580 --> 00:31:15,250
Did you buy it yourself? Where did you get the money?

493
00:31:16,670 --> 00:31:18,290
It's a used car.

494
00:31:18,290 --> 00:31:21,420
Mr. Zhao gave it to me.

495
00:31:21,420 --> 00:31:24,080
We're going to do big business together.

496
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:25,630
We're partners.

497
00:31:34,580 --> 00:31:35,330
Come down.

498
00:31:41,540 --> 00:31:42,290
Mumu.

499
00:31:42,630 --> 00:31:45,250
You've grown taller. You're so pretty now.

500
00:31:52,830 --> 00:31:56,000
You still can't afford a cochlear implant?

501
00:31:56,960 --> 00:32:00,670
I'm getting old so it's harder to make money now.

502
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:03,670
Mumu can't run around.

503
00:32:03,670 --> 00:32:06,380
She can't. Remember that.

504
00:32:06,380 --> 00:32:07,250
I'll remember.

505
00:32:54,210 --> 00:32:56,830
You went to sleep late last night,

506
00:32:56,830 --> 00:32:59,290
you're going to be late now, aren't you?

507
00:33:01,460 --> 00:33:04,460
You didn't get up early either.

508
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:08,210
Don't sign at school. Remember?

509
00:33:18,040 --> 00:33:19,040
Mumu.

510
00:33:25,460 --> 00:33:26,460
Come here, come here.

511
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:30,830
It's your first day of school.
Are you nervous?

512
00:33:33,540 --> 00:33:34,790
A gift for starting school.

513
00:33:34,790 --> 00:33:36,670
It's for you. Do you like it?

514
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:44,670
Come on.

515
00:33:51,830 --> 00:33:53,290
Let's give a warm welcome

516
00:33:53,290 --> 00:33:55,040
to our new classmate!

517
00:33:57,420 --> 00:34:00,580
Hello everyone, my name is Mumu.

518
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:03,170
Today, I'd like to introduce a new colleague, Xiao Ma.

519
00:34:03,170 --> 00:34:04,210
He's a bit special.

520
00:34:04,420 --> 00:34:05,920
He is a person with a hearing impairment.

521
00:34:07,750 --> 00:34:09,250
I'm Xiao Ma.

522
00:34:10,670 --> 00:34:12,960
I'm very happy to meet everyone.

523
00:34:13,130 --> 00:34:15,630
So, what do you like to do, Mumu?

524
00:34:16,460 --> 00:34:18,330
I like...

525
00:34:19,380 --> 00:34:21,380
I like...

526
00:34:23,250 --> 00:34:26,250
I like looking out the window.

527
00:34:26,750 --> 00:34:30,040
I also like helping my dad count money.

528
00:34:30,040 --> 00:34:32,290
I also like playing mahjong.

529
00:34:37,670 --> 00:34:40,080
Welcome.

530
00:34:40,290 --> 00:34:41,960
Happy.

531
00:34:42,290 --> 00:34:43,670
Good friend.

532
00:34:43,710 --> 00:34:46,580
Handsome.

533
00:34:48,670 --> 00:34:49,460
You have to remember,
to knock a lot.

534
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:59,080
Anyone who has seen the ocean, please raise your hands.

535
00:35:00,830 --> 00:35:02,290
So many of you have seen it!

536
00:35:02,710 --> 00:35:03,290
Okay.
Put your hands down.

537
00:35:11,830 --> 00:35:14,330
The little pigeon is talking.

538
00:36:20,210 --> 00:36:22,040
I didn't ask you to clean the room.

539
00:36:29,420 --> 00:36:31,920
Can you teach me sign language?

540
00:36:35,170 --> 00:36:36,880
This is "Okay."

541
00:36:38,210 --> 00:36:39,170
"Pretty."

542
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:02,920
Sorry,

543
00:37:03,540 --> 00:37:04,330
I'm late.

544
00:37:05,170 --> 00:37:06,670
Say goodbye to your classmates.

545
00:37:06,710 --> 00:37:08,960
Bye-bye.

546
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:21,830
Hong Jie.

547
00:37:27,750 --> 00:37:29,500
We used to work together.

548
00:37:30,540 --> 00:37:31,790
I was bullied.

549
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:33,790
So many people were watching,

550
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:36,580
but only he stood up for me.

551
00:37:40,710 --> 00:37:41,830
He fought with someone,

552
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:44,040
and got a scar from it.

553
00:37:47,790 --> 00:37:49,170
He was good to me.

554
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:51,290
And he could always make me laugh.

555
00:37:52,460 --> 00:37:54,380
I just wanted to be with him.

556
00:37:54,790 --> 00:37:56,580
